WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:12.776 --> 00:00:17.186
What are you doing on this stage
你站在这个舞台上做什么？

2
00:00:17.210 --> 00:00:20.328
in front of all these people?
还当着这么多人的面？

3
00:00:20.352 --> 00:00:21.726
(Laughter)
（笑声）

4
00:00:21.750 --> 00:00:22.901
Run!
快逃！

5
00:00:22.925 --> 00:00:23.928
(Laughter)
（笑声）

6
00:00:23.952 --> 00:00:25.130
Run now.
马上逃跑！

7
00:00:26.554 --> 00:00:29.521
That's the voice of my anxiety talking.
这是我内心的紧张情绪在说话。

8
00:00:30.359 --> 00:00:33.295
Even when there's absolutely nothing wrong,
即便一切都进行得很顺利，

9
00:00:33.319 --> 00:00:37.278
I sometimes get this overwhelming sense of doom,
我也经常会有这种巨大的挫败感，

10
00:00:37.302 --> 00:00:40.264
like danger is lurking just around the corner.
总觉得危险无处不在。

11
00:00:40.877 --> 00:00:42.993
You see, a few years ago,
几年前，

12
00:00:43.017 --> 00:00:45.514
I was diagnosed with generalized anxiety
我被诊断出患有焦虑症，

13
00:00:45.538 --> 00:00:46.688
and depression --
和抑郁症——

14
00:00:47.109 --> 00:00:49.529
two conditions that often go hand in hand.
这两种疾病经常会同时发生。

15
00:00:49.893 --> 00:00:54.158
Now, there was a time I wouldn't have told anybody,
这段经历我本不愿跟任何人分享，

16
00:00:54.182 --> 00:00:56.642
especially not in front of a big audience.
尤其是当着这么多人的面。

17
00:00:56.666 --> 00:00:58.193
As a black woman,
作为一名黑人女性，

18
00:00:58.217 --> 00:01:01.857
I've had to develop extraordinary resilience to succeed.
我必须有极强的 适应能力才能取得成功。

19
00:01:01.881 --> 00:01:03.860
And like most people in my community,
如同我社区中的大部分人一样，

20
00:01:03.884 --> 00:01:07.692
I had the misconception that depression was a sign of weakness,
我误以为抑郁症是软弱的表现，

21
00:01:07.716 --> 00:01:09.252
a character flaw.
是一种人格缺陷。

22
00:01:09.276 --> 00:01:10.850
But I wasn't weak;
但我并不软弱，

23
00:01:10.874 --> 00:01:12.344
I was a high achiever.
我还蛮成功的。

24
00:01:12.745 --> 00:01:14.948
I'd earned a Master's degree in Media Studies
我获得了媒体研究的硕士学位，

25
00:01:14.972 --> 00:01:19.081
and had a string of high-profile jobs in the film and television industries.
在电影和电视行业 有一系列不错的履历。

26
00:01:19.554 --> 00:01:22.604
I'd even won two Emmy Awards for my hard work.
我的出色表现 还让我获得了两次艾美奖。

27
00:01:23.256 --> 00:01:26.272
Sure, I was totally spent,
没错，我感到精疲力尽，

28
00:01:26.296 --> 00:01:28.966
I lacked interest in things I used to enjoy,
我对之前喜欢的事情丧失了兴趣，

29
00:01:28.990 --> 00:01:30.288
barely ate,
茶饭不思，

30
00:01:30.312 --> 00:01:32.215
struggled with insomnia
被失眠所困扰，

31
00:01:32.239 --> 00:01:34.863
and felt isolated and depleted.
觉得孤单和消沉。

32
00:01:35.382 --> 00:01:36.734
But depressed?
但是抑郁症？

33
00:01:36.758 --> 00:01:38.282
No, not me.
跟我没什么关系吧。

34
00:01:39.741 --> 00:01:41.947
It took weeks before I could admit it,
过了好几周我才承认，

35
00:01:41.971 --> 00:01:43.400
but the doctor was right:
医生是对的，

36
00:01:43.424 --> 00:01:44.702
I was depressed.
我的确抑郁了。

37
00:01:45.231 --> 00:01:48.779
Still, I didn't tell anybody about my diagnosis.
但我仍然没有告诉任何人。

38
00:01:49.342 --> 00:01:50.955
I was too ashamed.
我觉得羞愧难当。

39
00:01:50.979 --> 00:01:53.496
I didn't think I had the right to be depressed.
我从没想过我也有抑郁的权利。

40
00:01:54.238 --> 00:01:55.868
I had a privileged life
我生活条件优越，

41
00:01:55.892 --> 00:01:58.992
with a loving family and a successful career.
家庭幸福，事业有成。

42
00:01:59.528 --> 00:02:02.120
And when I thought about the unspeakable horrors
尤其当我想到， 正因为我的祖先们在这个国家

43
00:02:02.144 --> 00:02:04.632
that my ancestors had been through in this country
遭受到那些无法描述的苦难，

44
00:02:04.656 --> 00:02:06.624
so that I could have it better,
所以我才能过得好一些，

45
00:02:06.648 --> 00:02:08.326
my shame grew even deeper.
我就越发感到愧疚。

46
00:02:08.800 --> 00:02:10.893
I was standing on their shoulders.
我是站在他们肩膀上的。

47
00:02:10.917 --> 00:02:12.519
How could I let them down?
我怎么能让他们失望呢？

48
00:02:13.202 --> 00:02:15.255
I would hold my head up,
我只能昂起头，

49
00:02:15.279 --> 00:02:17.639
put a smile on my face
面带微笑，

50
00:02:17.663 --> 00:02:19.371
and never tell a soul.
不对任何人说。

51
00:02:22.286 --> 00:02:25.563
On July 4, 2013,
2013年7月4日，

52
00:02:26.299 --> 00:02:28.487
my world came crashing in on me.
我的世界彻底崩溃了。

53
00:02:29.219 --> 00:02:32.120
That was the day I got a phone call from my mom
我接到母亲的电话，

54
00:02:31.636 --> 00:02:36.419
telling me that my 22-year-old nephew, Paul, had ended his life,
说我22岁的侄子，保罗， 在与焦虑症和抑郁症抗争多年之后，

55
00:02:36.358 --> 00:02:38.999
after years of battling depression and anxiety.
结束了自己的生命。

56
00:02:40.488 --> 00:02:43.643
There are no words that can describe the devastation I felt.
没有语言足以形容我的绝望。

57
00:02:44.487 --> 00:02:45.781
Paul and I were very close,
我跟保罗很亲密，

58
00:02:45.805 --> 00:02:47.859
but I had no idea he was in so much pain.
但我从来不知道 他遭受着如此大的痛苦。

59
00:02:48.516 --> 00:02:52.074
Neither one of us had ever talked to the other about our struggles.
我们也从未跟对方提起过 自己的挣扎与抗争。

60
00:02:52.098 --> 00:02:54.262
The shame and stigma kept us both silent.
羞愧与耻辱感让我俩都保持沉默。

61
00:02:54.625 --> 00:03:00.113
Now, my way of dealing with adversity is to face it head on,
现在，我应对逆境的方式 就是昂首向前，

62
00:03:00.008 --> 00:03:03.166
so I spent the next two years researching depression and anxiety,
接下来我花了两年时间 来研究抑郁症和焦虑症，

63
00:03:03.190 --> 00:03:05.957
and what I found was mind-blowing.
而结果让我大吃一惊。

64
00:03:06.584 --> 00:03:08.558
The World Health Organization reports
根据世界卫生组织的报告，

65
00:03:08.582 --> 00:03:13.806
that depression is the leading cause of sickness and disability
抑郁症是在世界范围内 导致疾病和伤残

66
00:03:13.830 --> 00:03:15.169
in the world.
最主要的原因。

67
00:03:15.859 --> 00:03:18.850
While the exact cause of depression isn't clear,
导致抑郁症的准确原因尚不清楚，

68
00:03:18.874 --> 00:03:21.972
research suggests that most mental disorders develop,
研究显示，大部分精神疾病的发生，

69
00:03:21.996 --> 00:03:23.723
at least in part,
至少有一部分原因，

70
00:03:23.747 --> 00:03:26.402
because of a chemical imbalance in the brain,
是因为大脑化学物质的不平衡，

71
00:03:26.426 --> 00:03:30.328
and/or an underlying genetic predisposition.
以及/或者潜在的遗传易感性。

72
00:03:30.861 --> 00:03:33.022
So you can't just shake it off.
因此你无法根除它。

73
00:03:34.727 --> 00:03:36.458
For black Americans,
对于美国黑人而言，

74
00:03:36.482 --> 00:03:40.538
stressors like racism and socioeconomic disparities
来自种族歧视和 社会经济差异上的压力

75
00:03:40.562 --> 00:03:45.602
put them at a 20 percent greater risk of developing a mental disorder,
使他们患上心理疾病的 几率要高20%，

76
00:03:45.626 --> 00:03:48.038
yet they seek mental health services
然而他们寻求心理治疗的比例

77
00:03:48.062 --> 00:03:50.801
at about half the rate of white Americans.
仅仅达到美国白人的一半左右。

78
00:03:51.364 --> 00:03:54.214
One reason is the stigma,
原因之一就是感到羞耻，

79
00:03:54.238 --> 00:04:00.455
with 63 percent of black Americans mistaking depression for a weakness.
有63%的美国黑人将抑郁症 误认为是软弱的表现。

80
00:04:01.423 --> 00:04:05.681
Sadly, the suicide rate among black children
令人悲伤的是，黑人儿童的自杀率

81
00:04:05.705 --> 00:04:08.392
has doubled in the past 20 years.
在过去20年里增加了一倍。

82
00:04:09.663 --> 00:04:11.868
Now, here's the good news:
当然，也有好消息：

83
00:04:12.423 --> 00:04:16.705
seventy percent of people struggling with depression will improve
受到抑郁症困扰的人， 在治疗和药物的帮助下，

84
00:04:16.729 --> 00:04:20.086
with therapy, treatment and medication.
有70%情况会有所好转。

85
00:04:21.278 --> 00:04:22.940
Armed with this information,
掌握了这些信息后，

86
00:04:22.964 --> 00:04:24.671
I made a decision:
我做出了一个决定：

87
00:04:24.695 --> 00:04:27.663
I wasn't going to be silent anymore.
我不会再沉默下去。

88
00:04:28.560 --> 00:04:30.363
With my family's blessing,
有家人的祝福，

89
00:04:30.387 --> 00:04:32.280
I would share our story
我要把我们的故事分享出去，

90
00:04:32.304 --> 00:04:35.118
in hopes of sparking a national conversation.
希望能引发一场全国性的大讨论。

91
00:04:35.960 --> 00:04:38.731
A friend, Kelly Pierre-Louis, said,
我的一个朋友， 凯丽·皮埃尔-露易丝说，

92
00:04:38.755 --> 00:04:41.246
"Being strong is killing us."
“逞强在毁掉我们。”

93
00:04:42.563 --> 00:04:43.982
She's right.
她说的没错。

94
00:04:44.006 --> 00:04:48.028
We have got to retire those tired, old narratives
我们要摈弃那些老旧过时的叙述，

95
00:04:48.052 --> 00:04:49.607
of the strong black woman
比如坚强的黑人女性，

96
00:04:49.631 --> 00:04:51.841
and the super-masculine black man,
无比阳刚的黑人男性，

97
00:04:51.865 --> 00:04:54.785
who, no matter how many times they get knocked down,
他们无论被击倒多少次，

98
00:04:54.809 --> 00:04:57.044
just shake it off and soldier on.
都会爬起来，拍拍灰，继续前进。

99
00:04:57.590 --> 00:05:01.305
Having feelings isn't a sign of weakness.
感情丰富并不是软弱的标志。

100
00:05:02.341 --> 00:05:04.224
Feelings mean we're human.
那意味着我们还有人性。

101
00:05:04.670 --> 00:05:06.689
And when we deny our humanity,
如果我们连自己的人性都否定了，

102
00:05:06.713 --> 00:05:08.829
it leaves us feeling empty inside,
那就成了空心人，

103
00:05:08.853 --> 00:05:11.857
searching for ways to self-medicate in order to fill the void.
终日寻找自我治疗的良药， 填补内心的空白。

104
00:05:12.405 --> 00:05:15.150
My drug was high achievement.
我的良药就是巨大的成功。

105
00:05:16.191 --> 00:05:19.492
These days, I share my story openly,
这些天来，我公开分享自己的故事，

106
00:05:19.516 --> 00:05:21.726
and I ask others to share theirs, too.
我也鼓励大家分享自己的。

107
00:05:22.226 --> 00:05:23.674
I believe that's what it takes
我坚信必须这么做才能

108
00:05:23.698 --> 00:05:26.293
to help people who may be suffering in silence
帮助那些在沉默中忍受痛苦的人们

109
00:05:26.317 --> 00:05:28.526
to know that they are not alone
让他们知道自己并不孤独，

110
00:05:28.550 --> 00:05:30.235
and to know that with help,
让他们相信自己需要帮助，

111
00:05:30.259 --> 00:05:31.600
they can heal.
是可以被治愈的。

112
00:05:31.624 --> 00:05:33.789
Now, I still have my struggles,
现在我依然在遭受痛苦，

113
00:05:33.813 --> 00:05:36.101
particularly with the anxiety,
主要还是焦虑症，

114
00:05:36.125 --> 00:05:37.728
but I'm able to manage it
但我可以控制它，

115
00:05:37.752 --> 00:05:42.626
through daily mediation, yoga and a relatively healthy diet.
通过每天服药，练瑜伽 以及“相对健康的”饮食。

116
00:05:42.650 --> 00:05:43.718
(Laughter)
（笑声）

117
00:05:43.742 --> 00:05:45.964
If I feel like things are starting to spiral,
一旦我感觉自己状态不好了，

118
00:05:45.988 --> 00:05:48.032
I make an appointment to see my therapist,
我就会约我的治疗师见面，

119
00:05:48.056 --> 00:05:51.119
a dynamic black woman named Dawn Armstrong,
她是一位充满活力的黑人女性叫 道恩·阿姆斯特朗，

120
00:05:51.143 --> 00:05:53.116
who has a great sense of humor
她很幽默，

121
00:05:53.140 --> 00:05:55.377
and a familiarity that I find comforting.
很亲切，让我感到安心。

122
00:05:56.946 --> 00:05:58.584
I will always regret
我一直非常后悔

123
00:05:59.210 --> 00:06:01.276
that I couldn't be there for my nephew.
没有能为我侄子做些什么。

124
00:06:02.046 --> 00:06:03.833
But my sincerest hope
但我真诚地希望

125
00:06:04.515 --> 00:06:07.586
is that I can inspire others with the lesson that I've learned.
能让大家吸取我的教训。

126
00:06:11.002 --> 00:06:13.472
Life is beautiful.
生命是美丽的。

127
00:06:14.466 --> 00:06:16.028
Sometimes it's messy,
有时候也会不顺利，

128
00:06:16.052 --> 00:06:17.986
and it's always unpredictable.
永远充满未知。

129
00:06:18.854 --> 00:06:20.057
But it will all be OK
但一切都会好起来的，

130
00:06:20.081 --> 00:06:22.866
when you have your support system to help you through it.
只要拥有能帮助到你的体制。

131
00:06:23.333 --> 00:06:25.754
I hope that if your burden gets too heavy,
希望你们在撑不住的时候，

132
00:06:25.778 --> 00:06:27.484
you'll ask for a hand, too.
也会去寻求帮助。

133
00:06:27.508 --> 00:06:28.675
Thank you.
谢谢大家。

134
00:06:28.699 --> 00:06:31.581
(Applause)
（掌声）